.TH LPF-CONFIRM 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.3" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-confirm \- confirm a pending guarded apply
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf confirm
.SH DESCRIPTION
Confirm a pending guarded apply and promote it to known\-good state.
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf confirm
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
/var/lib/lpf/history
/var/lib/lpf/rollback
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Confirm only after verifying management access and expected traffic behavior.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-apply(8), lpf\-rollback(8)
